<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Phase 1: Docker (Before OBI) on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/</link><description>Recent content in Phase 1: Docker (Before OBI) on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>1. Configure and Start the Stack</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/1-configure-and-start/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/1-configure-and-start/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="add-your-splunk-credentials"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Add Your Splunk Credentials&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#add-your-splunk-credentials" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; obtain your &lt;code&gt;ACCESS_TOKEN&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;REALM&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;INSTANCE&lt;/code&gt; in your environment. You will need to paste them into configs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;$ACCESS_TOKEN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;$REALM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;$INSTANCE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Navigate to the Phase 1/2 directory and open &lt;code&gt;docker-compose.yaml&lt;/code&gt; in your editor:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~/workshop/obi/02-obi-docker
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;vim docker-compose.yaml &lt;span class="c1"&gt;#or editor of choice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Find the &lt;code&gt;splunk-otel-collector&lt;/code&gt; service and replace the four placeholder values with your real credentials:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. Generate Traffic</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/2-generate-traffic/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/2-generate-traffic/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="hit-the-frontend"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Hit the Frontend&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#hit-the-frontend" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use curl to generate traffic:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;curl -s http://localhost:3000/create-order &lt;span class="p"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; jq&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should see a JSON response like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-json" data-lang="json"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;#34;order&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;confirmed&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;#34;payment&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;#34;status&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;success&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;#34;transaction_id&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;txn-a1b2c3d4e5f6&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nt"&gt;&amp;#34;amount&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The request flowed through all three services. But right now, nobody is watching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="look-at-the-code"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Look at the Code&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#look-at-the-code" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take a moment to inspect the source code and confirm there is zero instrumentation:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Check Splunk</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/3-check-splunk/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/instrumentation/16-obi-ebpf/3-docker-before-obi/3-check-splunk/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="verify-infrastructure-metrics"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Verify Infrastructure Metrics&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#verify-infrastructure-metrics" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open &lt;a href="https://app.us1.signalfx.com/#/metrics" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Metric Finder&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 (or &lt;a href="https://app.us1.signalfx.com/#/chart/new?template=default&amp;amp;filters=sf_metric%3Aworkshop_heartbeat" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;make a chart&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
) and search for &lt;code&gt;workshop_heartbeat&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You should see the metric with &lt;code&gt;host.name&lt;/code&gt; matching your &lt;code&gt;WORKSHOP_HOST_NAME&lt;/code&gt; value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search for that &lt;code&gt;host.name&lt;/code&gt; to see what other metrics the collector is sending (CPU, memory, disk, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id="confirm-apm-is-empty"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Confirm APM is Empty&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#confirm-apm-is-empty" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>